# requirements.in — source for `requirements.lock` (deterministic runtime deps).
#
# This file pins ONLY runtime dependencies — dev/test tools (pytest, ruff,
# mypy, pip-tools itself, sentence-transformers, etc.) come from the
# [dependency-groups.dev] table in pyproject.toml and are intentionally NOT
# locked here so that `pip install -r requirements.lock` produces a clean
# runtime-only install for production deployments.
#
# Regenerate the lockfile with:
#   .venv/bin/pip-compile requirements.in --output-file requirements.lock --resolver=backtracking
#
# The lockfile is consumed by:
#   - Production Docker / Homebrew bottle builds (deterministic deploys)
#   - tools/license_check.py (gates merges on licence-safe transitive deps)
-e .
